Marketing Brief:
   Noted....
PUBLISHING: Franklin Electronic Publishers Inc. signed an
exclusive agreement with Little, Brown  Co. for the
publication of Little Brown's "Manual of Medical
Therapeutics" as a hand-held, pocket-sized electronic book.
The electronic medical reference book, which will be on a
computer card, will be available in the fourth quarter,
Franklin said.
                                                                                                       

   WHO'S NEWS: Macmillan/McGraw-Hill School Publishing Co.
said Richard T. Morgan, its president and chief executive
officer, will retire in May upon reaching age 55. Dr. Morgan
said he plans to take a long vacation and write mathematics
textbooks. A new chief executive is expected to be named
within a few weeks. Macmillan/McGraw-Hill School Publishing
Co. is a joint venture of McGraw-Hill Inc. and Macmillan
Inc., a unit of Maxwell Communication Corp. . . . J. Manuel
Calvo, 42, was named to the new post of vice president of
programming, production and promotion at Telemundo Group
Inc., a TV network operator. He was vice president and
general manager of WSCV/Channel 51, one of Telemundo's
stations in Miami.